  "explanation": "The defendant committed a significant breach of fiduciary duty as an accountant by embezzling $25,000. However, as a first-time offender who has already begun the process of restitution by partially paying back the funds, a lengthy custodial sentence is not warranted. The outbursts from spectators are legally irrelevant to the sentencing guidelines. A six-month sentence accounts for the breach of professional trust while recognizing the mitigating factors of a clean criminal record and proactive repayment.",
  "verdict": 6
}
